HEADWORD: Tracheobranchia
<hw>Tra`che*o*bran"chi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Tracheobranchlae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Trachea</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the gill-like breathing organs of certain
aquatic insect larvae. They contain tracheal tubes somewhat similar to
those of other insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

